### 3 Â· Objects (always `.strict()` unless you **want** extras)
```ts
const ProfileSchema = z.object({
  id:         z.string().uuid().describe("Primary key"),
  username:   z.string().min(3).max(16),
  bio:        z.string().max(160).optional(),
  created_at: z.date(),
}).strict();               // âŸµ additionalProperties = false

type Profile = z.infer<typeof ProfileSchema>; // static TS type
```

Need a â€œbag of extrasâ€? swap `.strict()` for `.passthrough()` (keeps unknown keys) or `.catchall(z.unknown())`.

